parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Leaking front fork seals can cause a loss of control, wobbling, and instability while riding, which can lead to accidents and injuries.
symptoms: Front fork seals are leaking
shock absorbers for the front end of the motorcycle are faulty
the motorcycle wobbles or shakes at high speeds (around 75-80 mph)
loss of control while riding.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden stalling of the engine can cause loss of power, leading to a loss of control, and potentially resulting in accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The engine stalls without warning
the vehicle loses power
the vehicle stalls while driving at high speeds
the vehicle stalls without any indication or warning.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Excessive oil consumption can lead to engine damage, premature wear, and potentially cause engine failure, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The engine is blowing out oil
the oil level is consistently low
the vehicle is consuming excessive amounts of oil
the engine is making loud noises or knocking sounds.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Premature wear of rear brakes can lead to reduced stopping power, increased stopping distance, and potentially cause accidents.
symptoms: Rear brake pads wear out excessively
rear rotors show signs of wear
squealing or grinding noise when applying the brakes
vibrations when braking
reduced braking performance.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: An electrical short circuit can cause damage to the vehicle's battery, leading to unexpected stalls, loss of power, and potentially even a fire, which can compromise vehicle safety and leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle's battery is draining rapidly
the battery is overheating
there is a burning smell or smoke coming from the vehicle
the electrical system is malfunctioning
the vehicle's lights or accessories are not functioning properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure to honor the windshield recall can lead to a compromised windshield, which can cause reduced visibility, increased risk of injury, and potentially lead to accidents.
symptoms: The dealer refused to replace the windshield despite the recall
the windshield is cracked or damaged
the windshield is not properly sealed
water leaks into the vehicle through the windshield.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Poor service from the dealer can lead to frustration, wasted time, and potentially compromise the safety and performance of the vehicle.
symptoms: The dealer refused to honor a recall
the dealer failed to diagnose or repair the issue correctly
the dealer did not provide adequate communication or updates
the dealer did not provide a loaner vehicle or alternative transportation.
